Privacy Policy
Privacy Policy
Published: April 1, 2021
Last updated: Feburary 14, 2024
We, BANDAI CO., LTD. respect your privacy. This privacy policy describes how we process Personal Data about you that we collect through the following ways:
Our website(s) where this privacy policy is published (“Website”);
Our software application(s) that we provide or is provided through a computer or mobile device (“App”);
Our social media pages where we include a link to this privacy policy (collectively “Social Media Page”);
HTML-formatted emails sent by us to you that link to this privacy policy or other communications with you; and
Our offline business interactions with you.
We call our Website, App, Social Media Page, emails and offline business interactions collectively the “Services.”
We process your personal data in accordance with applicable data protection laws, including the General Data Protection Regulation of the European Union (the “GDPR”), and the California Consumer Privacy Act, as amended (the “CCPA”).
1.WHAT CATEGORIES OF PERSONAL DATA WE COLLECT
“Personal Data” is information that identifies you as an individual or relates to an identifiable individual. The Services collect the following categories of Personal Data. The categories of Personal Data that we collect are different according to each Service, and each Service does not always collect all the categories of Personal Data below.
Name, including nickname and username on social media
Postal address, including billing address and shipping address
Phone number
Email address
Gender
Date of birth
User ID, including Bandai Namco ID, social media account ID
Password to log in
Inquiry and information necessary to respond to the inquiry
Your posted video or image
IP address, with which we may identify your approximate location
Login authentication history
History of use of our Services
2.HOW WE COLLECT YOUR PERSONAL DATA
We collect your Personal Data in different ways including:
・Through the Services
We collect your Personal Data through the Services, for example, when you sign up for a newsletter, register an account to access the Services, participate in our event, contact our customer service and place an order.
・Through Other Sources
- We receive your Personal Data from other sources, for example, X(formerly Twitter), when we run a campaign on X(formerly Twitter).
- When you connect your social media account to your Services accounts, you will share certain Personal Data from your social media account to us, for example, your name, email address, photo, list of social media contacts, and any other information that may become accessible or you make accessible to us when you connect your social media account to your Services accounts. We refer to this as “Social Sharing.”
We need to collect your Personal Data in order to provide you with the requested Services. If you do not provide the data we request for, we may not be able to provide the Services. When you disclose Personal Data about a person other than you to us or our service providers in connection with the Services, you represent you have the authority to do so and permit us to use the Personal Data in accordance with this privacy policy.
3.PURPOSES OF PROCESSING YOUR PERSONAL DATE
We and our service providers process your Personal Data for the following purposes:
・To provide the functionality of the Services and respond to your request
- Provide the functionality of the Services, including setting access to the registered account and providing related services to you.
- Respond to your inquiry and request when you contact us by our online contact form or other measures, for example, sending us an inquiry, proposal, or complaint.
- Complete your transaction, verify your data, and provide related services.
- Notify you of administrative information including changes to our terms and conditions and policies.
・To provide our newsletters and other marketing materials to you and facilitate Social Sharing
- Send marketing emails that contain information about our Services and new products, and other news regarding us.
- Facilitate the Social Sharing function that you choose to use.
・To analyze Personal Data for business reporting and personalized advertising
- Generate reports that aggregate and analyze trends of use of our digital contents and improve our Services by analyzing and predicting users’ preferences.
- Having better understanding of your interests and preferences, personalize our interactions with you and provide information and/or offers tailored to your interests.
- Having better understanding of your preferences, provide you through the Services with the contents that seem to be relevant and interesting to you.
・To permit you to participate in prize competitions, contests, and other sales promotion activities
- Decide whether you are qualified to join our promotion, ship a prize, and conduct other campaigns. We may establish additional rules regarding how we use and disclose your Personal Data for such promotions. Please check such additional rules before you choose to join our promotions.
・To aggregate Personal Data for our use
- We may aggregate Personal Data so that we no longer need to treat the data as Personal Data. You or other individuals cannot be identified by this process, and we use such aggregated data for our business purposes and generate non-personal data that we may disclose.
・To achieve our business purposes
More specifically,
- Improve the efficiency of our Services and sales promotion campaigns.
- Comply with legal, regulatory, or contractual requirements.
- Prevent unlawful activities and carry out security monitoring, including detecting and preventing cyberattacks or attempts of identity theft.
- Develop new products and services.
- Enhance, improve, repair, maintain, or modify our existing products and services, as well as undertake quality and safety assurance measures with you, to comply with a legal obligation, and/or based on our legitimate interest.
4.DISCLOSURE – To Whom We Disclose Your Personal Data
4.1.We disclose Personal Data:
・To our affiliates
We may disclose your Personal Data to our affiliates for the purposes described in this privacy policy. For example, we use Bandai Namco ID in certain Services, and Personal Data registered to Bandai Namco ID is disclosed to our affiliates in Japan. You can see the Services that use Bandai Namco ID here:
https://www.bandainamco.co.jp/en/about/grouplink.html.
Bandai Namco ID is a service managed by Bandai Namco Entertainment Inc.
We jointly use your personal data to the extent below.
Categories of Jointly Used Personal Data
Name, postal address, phone number, email address and IP address of a person who contacts our customer service center
Record of inquiries and our response
Other necessary information to manage inquiry response
Scope of Joint Users
BANDAI CO., LTD.
BANDAI SPIRITS CO., LTD.
Purpose for Joint Use
Respond to your inquiry and request when you contact us by our online contact form or other measures, for example, sending us an inquiry, proposal, or complaint.
Entity Responsible for Joint Use
BANDAI CO., LTD.
BANDAI SPIRITS CO., LTD.
For the purpose of this joint use, we and BANDAI SPIRITS CO., LTD. are joint controllers.
・To third party sponsors of prize competitions, contests, and other similar promotions. By using the Services, you may disclose your Personal Data by yourself.
Please note posts or information disclosed on message boards, chat, profile pages, blogs, and other services where you are able to post information or contents (including, but not limited to, our Social Media Pages) may become public and available to other uses and the general public.
If you connect your accounts of the Services to your social media accounts through Social Sharing, you share information with your friends who are related to your social media accounts, other users and providers of your social media accounts. We understand you permit us to facilitate the information sharing and use of the shared information is managed based on the privacy policy of the providers of the social media.
4.2.Disclosure to Other Recipients Than Those Listed Above
We also disclose your Personal Data as necessary or appropriate when it is legally required or permitted to do so as below:
・To comply with applicable law and regulations
Such laws may include those of a country other than your country of residence.
・To cooperate with public and government authorities
We may disclose your Personal Data to such authorities to respond to orders or provide information that we believe is necessary or appropriate. These authorities may include those of a country other than your country of residence.
・To cooperate with law enforcement authorities
We may also disclose your Personal Data, for example, when we respond to law enforcement authorities' requests and orders or provide information that we believe is important.
・For other legal reasons
We may also disclose your Personal Data if necessary to enforce our terms and conditions and to protect our rights, privacy, safety, or property, and/or that of our affiliates, you or others.
・In connection with a sale or business transaction
We may also disclose your Personal Data to a third party in the event of any reorganization, merger, sale, joint venture, assignment, transfer, or other disposition of all or any portion of our business, assets, or stock (including procedures in connection with any bankruptcy or similar proceedings).
5.OTHER DATA
We may also collect the followings categories of data in addition to those listed in section 1 above.
Browser and device information
App usage data
Information collected through cookies, pixel tags and other technologies
Demographic information and other information that does not reveal your specific identity
Information that has been aggregated in a manner that it no longer reveals your specific identity
5.1.Collection of Other Data
We and our service providers may collect your other data in different ways including:
・Your browser or device
Certain data are collected via most browsers or automatically through your devices, such as your Media Access Control (MAC) address, computer type (Windows or Mac), screen resolution, operating system name and version, device manufacturer and model, language, Internet browser type and version and the name and version of the Services (such as the App) you are using. We use these data to ensure that the Services function properly.
・Your Use of Our Apps
If you download and use the Apps, we and our service providers may track and collect the usage of the Apps including the date the Apps on your device access our servers and the data and types of files that are downloaded to the Apps based on your device number.
・Cookies
Cookies are pieces of data that is stored directly on the computer that you are using. Cookies allow us to collect data such as browser type, time spent on the Services, pages visited, language preferences, and other traffic data. We and our service providers use the data for security purposes, to facilitate navigation, to display information more effectively, and to personalize your experience. We also gather statistical information about use of the Services to continually improve the design and functionality, understand how they are used, and resolve issues regarding the Services. Cookies enables us to display what is likely to attract your interest among our advertisements and proposals while you are using the Services. We also use cookies or other technologies in online advertising to track responses to our advertisements. We currently do not support internet browsers' do-not-track signals. If you do not like your data to be collected by using cookies, most browsers allow you to choose to decline cookies automatically or accept or decline certain cookies from certain websites. For more information and to change your cookie settings, including withdrawal of your consent, visit our
Cookie Preference Center.
However, if you do not accept cookies, there may be some inconvenience in using the Services, and you may not be able to receive our advertising or other offers that relate to your interests or needs.
・Pixel Tags and Similar Technologies
We may use pixel tags (also known as web beacons or clear GIFs) to track the behavior of users of the Services (including email recipients), measure the conversion rate of our marketing campaigns, and compile statistics about the use and response rates of the Services.
・Analytic Technologies
We use Google Analytics, which collect and analyze data about the use of the Services and generate reports about activities and trends, based on cookies and similar technologies. This service may also obtain data about your use of other websites, apps and online resources. You may visit
www.google.com/policies/privacy/partners/
to learn about Google's practices and exercise the opt-out of Google Analytics by downloading a browser add-on available at
https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout.
・Adobe Flash Technologies
We may use Flash LSOs and other technologies to obtain and store data about your use of the Services. If you do not want Flash LSOs stored on your computer, you may change your Flash player settings to block the storage of Flash LSOs by using the tools contained in websites’ storage settings panel. You can also go to the global storage settings panel and follow the instructions (for example, how to remove an existing Flash LSO, which is called “information”, how to prevent Flash LSOs from being placed on your computer without you asking, and how to block Flash LSOs that have not been delivered by the operator of the webpage you are viewing may be explained). Please note that if you restrict acceptance of Flash LSOs, the functionality of some Flash applications may degrade or be interfered.
・Physical Location
We may obtain the physical location of your devices by using satellites, cell towers, or WiFi signals. Our Apps may obtain device location while running in the foreground or background. We may use the physical location of your device and provide you with personalized location-based services and content. We may also share the physical location of your device, combined with the advertisements you have viewed and other information we have obtained, with our marketing partners so that they can provide you with more personalized content and study the effectiveness of advertising campaigns. In some cases, you may be able to allow or deny such use or sharing of your device’s location information. However, in such cases, we or our marketing partners may not be able to provide you with personalized services and content.
5.2.Collection of Other Data
If it is required to treat the data listed in this section as Personal Data under applicable data protection laws, we process the data as Personal Data in accordance with this privacy policy.
If you use the Services via banners or other advertisements on advertising websites that we contract with, we use your visit history of the advertising websites to make payment to the websites.
6.SECURITY
We take reasonable organizational, technical and administrative measures to protect your Personal Data. If you have a reason to believe that there is a problem with our security, please immediately contact us in accordance with section 15 below.
7.YOUR CHOICE OVER OUR USE AND DISCLOSURE OF YOUR PERSONAL DATA
We provide you with options such as to refuse marketing purpose emails. Please refer to the instructions in the Services that you are using. If you have questions, please use inquiry forms of the Services or contact us at
ppolicy@bandai.co.jp
.
We will try to comply with your requests as soon as reasonably practicable. Please note that if you opt out of receiving marketing related emails from us, we may still send you important administrative messages, from which you cannot opt out.
8.YOUR LEGAL RIGHTS
If you would like to request to access, correct, update, restrict, limit or delete Personal Data, object to or opt out of the processing of Personal Data, or if you would like to receive a copy of your Personal Data to transmit them to another company (to the extent these rights are provided to you by applicable law), you may contact us according to section 15 below. We will respond to your request in accordance with applicable law.
In your request, please specify what Personal Data you would like us to change or whether you would like us to delete your Personal Data from our database. For your protection, we may only implement requests with respect to the Personal Data associated with the particular email address that you use to send us your request, and we may need to verify your identity before implementing your request. We will try to comply with your request as soon as reasonably practicable.
Please note that we may need to retain certain data for recordkeeping purposes or completing any transactions that you began prior to requesting a change or deletion. For example, when you make a purchase or join a sales promotion campaign, you may not be able to change or delete the Personal Data provided by you until such purchase or sales promotion is completed.
You can change Personal Data registered to Bandai Namco ID or delete your Bandai Namco ID at
https://www.bandainamcoid.com/portal/help?client_id=&backto=&open=13#.
You can change Personal Data registered to Premium Bandai or delete your Premium Bandai account at Premium Bandai my page.
9.RETENTION
We retain your Personal Data for as long as needed or permitted in light of the purposes for which they were obtained and consistent with applicable laws.
10.SERVICES BY THIRD PARTIES
