17.ADDITIONAL INFORMATION FOR OUR VISITORS FROM THE STATE OF CALIFORNIA
This section supplements our privacy policy and explains how we collect, use, disclose, sell, share, and protect personally identifiable information of California residents and any information related to it (“Personal Information”) and non-personal information.
I.NOTICE AT COLLECTION
i.CATEGORIES OF PERSONAL INFORMATION WE COLLECT
We collect the following categories of your Personal Information:
Categories of Personal Information We Collect as Stipulated in CCPA 1798.140.(v)(1)
Sources
a. Identifiers such as a real name, alias, postal address, unique personal identifier, online identifier, Internet Protocol address, email address, account name or other similar identifiers.
You, our affiliates
b. Characteristics of protected classifications under California or federal law (e.g., gender, age).
You
c. Commercial information, including records of products purchased, obtained or considered, or other purchasing or consuming histories or tendencies.
You, our affiliates
d. Internet or other electronic network activity information, including, but not limited to, browsing history, search history, and information regarding your interaction with our Websites, Apps, or advertisement.
You, our Websites/Apps/advertisement service providers, your device
e. Geolocation data.
You, your device
f. Audio, electronic, visual, thermal, olfactory, or similar information (e.g., recording of inquiry calls).
You
g. Inferences drawn from any of the above information to create a profile about you reflecting your preferences.
You, our affiliates, our data analytics providers
h. Sensitive Personal Information, which is Bandai Namco ID and account IDs of the Services in combination with the respective passwords to log in to the accounts
You, our affiliates
ii.BUSINESS OR COMMERCIAL PURPOSES FOR WHICH WE COLLECT PERSONAL INFORMATION
We collect and use your Personal Information listed in subsection i. above for the purposes described in section 3 of this privacy policy as below. Please see section 3 of this privacy policy above for the details of the purposes:
Purposes
Categories of Personal Information
(1) To provide the functionality of the Services and respond to your request
a, c, d, f, h
(2) To provide our newsletters and other marketing materials to you and facilitate social sharing
a, b, c, d, e, g
(3) To analyze Personal Data for business reporting and personalized advertising
a, c, d, e, g
(4) To permit you to participate in prize competitions, contests, and other sales promotion activities
a, d
(5) To aggregate Personal Data for our use
a, b, c, d, e, g
(6) To achieve our business purposes
a, b, c, d, e, f, g, h
iii.YOUR RIGHT TO OPT OUT OF SALE OR SHARING OF PERSONAL INFORMATION
We may “sell” or “share”, as defined in the CCPA, your Personal Information to/with third parties for the purposes (2) and (3) above. You have the right to opt out of the sale or sharing of your Personal Information to/with third parties. You can opt out of the sale or sharing of your Personal Information through the
Do Not Sell or Share My Personal Information
link or by submitting an opt-out request to us in accordance with subsection IV below.
iv.RETENTION
We retain your Personal Information for as long as needed or permitted in light of the purposes for which it was obtained and consistent with applicable laws.
II.YOUR PRIVACY RIGHTS
i.RIGHT TO KNOW ABOUT PERSONAL INFORMATION COLLECTED, DISCLOSED, SOLD OR SHARED
- The CCPA states that you have the right to request us to disclose what Personal Information we collect, use, disclose, sell and share.
- You can exercise your above-mentioned rights unless you have exercised the rights within the preceding 12 months. We endeavor to respond to you within 45 days of receiving a verifiable request from you. If you intend to exercise such rights, please refer to subsection IV below.
- We use your Personal Information (name, email address, Bandai Namco ID, and account ID of the Services) to verify your request. You may be asked to provide additional information so that we can verify your request.
- The categories of Personal Information we collected, business or commercial purpose, and sources within the preceding 12 months are as described in subsections I. i and I. ii above.
- The categories of Personal Information we have sold or shared to/with third parties, the business or commercial purposes for the sale or sharing, and the categories of such third parties are as follows:
Categories of Personal Information
Business or Commercial Purpose as Described in Section 5 of our Privacy Policy
Categories of Third Parties We Have Sold or Shared Personal Information
Identifiers such as an online identifier, Internet Protocol address, email address, account name or other similar identifiers.
Facilitate the social sharing function that you choose to use.
Social media platform providers
Identifiers such as an online identifier, Internet Protocol address, email address, account name or other similar identifiers.
Internet or other electronic network activity information, including, but not
Having better understanding of your interests and preferences, personalize our interactions with you and provide information and/or offers tailored to your interests.
Advertising technology partners
limited to, browsing history, search history, and information regarding your interaction with our Websites, Apps, or advertisement.
Geolocation data.
- Disclosure, Sale or Sharing of Personal Information of Children
We do not have actual knowledge that we sell or share Personal Information about California consumers who we know are younger than 16 years old.
Under the CCPA, “sell” means disclosing by electronic or other means, a consumer's Personal Information to a third party for monetary or other valuable consideration, and “share” means sharing by electronic or other means, a consumer's Personal Information with a third party for cross-context behavioral advertising, whether or not for monetary or other valuable consideration.
ii.RIGHT TO REQUEST DELETION OF PERSONAL INFORMATION
- The CCPA states that you have the right to request us to delete your Personal Information collected by us.
- You can exercise your above-mentioned right with your account with us, unless you have exercised the rights within the preceding 12 months. We endeavor to respond to you within 45 days of receiving a verifiable request. If you intend to exercise such rights, please refer to subsection IV below.
- We use your information (name, email address, Bandai Namco ID, and account ID of the Services) to verify your request. You may be asked to provide additional information so that we can verify your request.
iii. RIGHT TO REQUEST CORRECTION OF INACCURATE PERSONAL INFORMATION
- The CCPA states you have the right to request us to correct inaccurate Personal Information about you.
- You can exercise your above-mentioned rights, unless you have exercised the rights within preceding 12 months. We endeavor to respond to you within 45 days of receiving a verifiable request. If you intend to exercise such rights, please refer to subsection IV below.
- We use your information (name, email address, Bandai Namco ID, and account ID of the Services) to verify your request.
iv.RIGHT TO OPT-OUT OF THE SALE OR SHARING OF PERSONAL INFORMATION
- The CCPA states that you have the right to opt-out of the sale or sharing of your Personal Information by us.
- Under the CCPA, the activities, in which we disclose the information collected from cookies or email address to advertising agencies to manage our personalized advertising to those of you 16 years of age or older based on your preferences, may be considered a “sale” of personal information.
- Opt-out rights can be exercised by visiting our Cookie Policy or by going directly to our Cookie Settings page and deleting or preventing cookies from being used. You can also click on the “
Do Not Sell or Share My Personal Information
” link at the bottom of every webpage.
v.RIGHT TO LIMIT THE USE AND DISCLOSURE OF SENSITIVE PERSONAL INFORMATION
- We collect your Bandai Namco ID and account IDs of the Services in combination with passwords to log in to the accounts, which are sensitive Personal Information under the CCPA. We do not use or disclose the sensitive Personal Information for any purposes other than those authorized under the CCPA, including performing the services or providing the goods requested by you.
vi.RIGHT TO NON-DISCRIMINATION FOR THE EXERCISE OF A CONSUMER’S PRIVACY RIGHT
- The CCPA states that you have a right not to receive discriminatory treatment by us for the exercise of the privacy rights conferred by the CCPA.
III.AUTHORIZED AGENT
When you use an authorized agent to submit a request to know, a request to delete, or a request to correct inaccurate Personal information, we may require that you:
- Provide the authorized agent with written permission to do so and verify your own identity directly with us.
- Directly confirm with us that you provided the authorized agent with permission to submit the request.
We may deny a request from an agent that does not submit a proof that they have been authorized by you to act on your own behalf.
IV.CONTACT US
Please contact us by email if you have any questions or concerns about this privacy policy or the information we hold about you.
- Email address:
ppolicy@bandai.co.jp
- Data Protection Officer:
bnhd-dpo-office@iij.ad.jp
V.HOW OUR WEBSITE RESPOND TO OPT-OUT PREFERENCE SIGNALS
Some web browsers incorporate an Opt-out preference signal feature that sends signals to websites you visit that you want to opt out from the sale or share of your Personal Information. Our website responds to Opt-out preference signals. You can confirm your settings by going directly to our
Cookie Settings page
. You can also click on the “
Do Not Sell or Share My Personal Information
” link at the bottom of every webpage.
VI.CHILDREN'S PRIVACY
We do not collect and store Personal Information about children (in this provision, we define children as those who are under 13 years of age) if this information is submitted by a child without prior parental consent or by the parent or guardian of the child.
If we discover that we've unintentionally collected information from a child in a way that does not meet the requirements under the CCPA and other applicable laws, we will delete the information immediately.
We use cookies to improve your experience on our website, to personalise content and ads, to provide social media features and to analyse our traffic.
We share information about your use of our website with our social media, advertising and analytics partners, who may combine it with other information that you have provided to them or that they have collected from your use of their services.
We do not set and use cookies for the purpose of improving your website experience or advertisement or social media features or web access analytics for our users under 16 years of age.
Please click “Reject All Cookies” if you are below the age of 16. Please click “Accept All Cookies” if you are 16 years of age or older, and accept all cookies. To customize your cookie settings, please click “Cookies Settings”.
